==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: heroin
<hw>her"o*in</hw> <pr>(h⟦etil⟧r"⟦osl⟧*⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>a morphine derivative, <altname>diacetyl
morphine</altname>, used to relieve severe pain and as a sedative. It is
highly addictive, and its use is strictly controlled in the U.S. by
federal law. It is a popular strong narcotic drug of abuse, in part
because it is more soluble than morphine. It is sometimes included as
one of the components of <partof>Brompton's mixture</partof>, used to
control pain in terminallly ill patients.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> diacetyl morphine, H, horse, junk, scag, shit,
smack.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heroine</ent>⟦br⟧
